Chairman/CEO, Nigerians in Diaspora Commission (NIDCOM)  Hon Abike Dabiri-Erewa has given renewed hope again to the 485 Nigerian voluntary Returnees from South Africa to fast track their reintegration and stabilization through the signing of an MOU with the Small and Medium Enterprises Development Agency of Nigeria, SMEDAN. The NIDCOM Chairman disclosed this on Wednesday when she paid a courtesy visit to the Director-General/CEO of SMEDAN Dr Dikko Umaru in Abuja. N33bn MSME zonal intervention projects fund unaccounted for… Villa security beats up journalist for snapping pictures Nigeria, South Africa to implement `Early Warning Signal` ―… Google, SMEDAN train 80 youths on digital marketing ALSO READ: 3200 persons killed by tankers, trailers in four years ― FRSC Mrs Abike Dabiri-Erewa added that the Returnees need to be reassured that President Muhammadu Buhari has not and will not abandon them but will ensure they are fully engaged and reintegrated. The Director-General SMEDAN, Dr Umaru also commended the NIDCOM Chairman/CEO for her untiring efforts at passionately handling issues affecting Nigerians in Diaspora, urging never to be discouraged but to remain undaunted. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
